1. Security and Compliance Requirements:

   a. All implementations must maintain SOC 2 Type II compliance for document handling
      and processing operations, with annual third-party audits.
   
   b. GDPR compliance must be maintained for all operations involving EU resident data,
      including but not limited to:
      - Implementation of data encryption at rest and in transit
      - Proper data subject access rights implementation
      - Data minimization and retention policies
      - Breach notification procedures
   
   c. HIPAA compliance must be maintained for all medical document processing,
      including:
      - Encryption of Protected Health Information (PHI)
      - Access controls and audit logging
      - Business Associate Agreement requirements
      - Security incident procedures

2. Data Protection Obligations:

   a. All document storage implementations must use AES-256 encryption or stronger.
   
   b. Access control systems must implement role-based access control (RBAC).
   
   c. Security monitoring and audit logging must be maintained with a minimum
      90-day retention period.
   
   d. Regular security assessments must be conducted at least quarterly.

3. Distribution Requirements:

   a. Source code distributions must maintain all security controls and compliance
      features.
   
   b. Binary distributions must include all required security features and
      compliance capabilities.
   
   c. Modified versions must maintain compliance with all security and regulatory
      requirements.

4. Notice Requirements:

The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all
copies or substantial portions of the Software.

